  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">RSE COVID Jalles</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed investment consists of a senior loan to Jalles Machado S.A. (Jalles, Jalles Machado or the Company), composed of (i) an A Loan of up to US$20 million or the BRL equivalent, and (ii) a B Loan of up to US$7.5 million. The Company is playing an important role in the COVID-19 response in the state of Goias, ensuring a continuous supply of sanitizing products in this frontier region.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">By sustaining the Company&apos;s operations, the project helps consumers have continued access to hand sanitizer and ensures continuity of employment opportunities in a frontier region. By limiting supply disruptions, the project promotes resilience in the sugar and ethanol sector.</narrative>
  </description>
